In the Matter of the Estate of Henry Brien, Deceased. Annie A. Coulson, as Executrix and Trustee, Appellant; Jean H. Buller et al., Respondents and Appellants; Jessie B. Tunstall, as Temporary Administratrix of the Estate of Robert Brien, Deceased, Respondent. Argued May 16,1938; decided May 31,1938. *580Edward E. Beichman, Sydney A. Luria and Alfred B. Carb for appellant. Bobert H. Koehler, Daniel J. Madigan, John J. Boyle, C. Frank Beams and Martin D. Jacobs for appellants and respondents. Banton Moore, in person, and Walter L. Post for Banton Moore, respondent.

Concur: Crane, Ch. J., Lehman, O’Brien, Hubbs, Loughran, Finch and Rifpey, JJ.

Edward E. Beichman, Sydney A. Luria and Alfred B. Carb for Jessie B. Tunstall, as administratrix, respondent. Order affirmed, without costs; no opinion.
